title: Appointment to the Steering Committee on Study of Family Commission
content_text:
p>
The Government today (March 29) announced the appointment of the incoming 
Chairman of the Commission on Youth Mr Joseph Lee Chung-tak and the 
re-appointment of the commission's outgoing chairman, Dr Philemon Choi Yuen-wan, 
to the Steering Committee on Study of Family Commission from April 1 to June 30, 
2007. A spokesman for the Health, Welfare and Food Bureau said that since Mr Lee would 
take up the chairmanship of the Commission on Youth on April 1, he would become

take up the chairmanship of the Commission on Youth on April 1, he would become 
an ex-officio member of the steering committee from this date. Also, Dr Choi 
would be re-appointed in his personal capacity as a non-official member on the 
same date. The steering committee is tasked to study whether a Family Commission 
responsible for policies and initiatives relating to family support should be 
set up, and if so, the re-organisation and resource re-allocation that need to

follow. The report on the study is expected to be finished by mid-2007. The Chief Executive announced in his 2006-07 Policy Address that the 
Administration would seriously study whether an integrated, holistic and 
high-level Family Commission should be established to study and address problems 
from a cross-policy perspective with a view to achieving more effective 
co-ordination of policies and initiatives relating to family support. To take 
the study forward, the Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food set up a Steering

the study forward, the Secretary for Health, Welfare and Food set up a Steering Committee in December, 2006, to advise on the study. The membership of the steering committee from April 1 is as follows: Chairperson
